# mv


# What happens when you execute the “move” (mv) command to move the file into the new directory?
# The moved "assignment.txt" file replaces the old "assignment.txt" file that was in the "projects" directory with no warning


# mv having two commands
# first specify the file
# second specify the destination / new name of the file (or combined)


# if you want to move a dir
# you should add slash after the destinated dir
# or else the destinated dir will be replaced


